            <div type="apparatus"/>
                
            
            
            <div type="translation" source="bib:Hultzsch1890_01">
                
                <p>In order that (<hi rend="italic">the god</hi>) <hi rend="bold">Kumāra-svāmin</hi> at the gate of the <hi rend="italic">gopura</hi> might protect<note><foreign>la<hi rend="grantha">kṣi</hi>kka</foreign> seems to be a vulgar form for <foreign><hi rend="grantha">rakṣi</hi>kka</foreign>.</note> (<hi rend="italic">him</hi>), the magistrate (<hi rend="italic">adhikārin</hi>) <hi rend="bold">Chandra-piḷḷai</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kāṭṭeri</hi> (<hi rend="italic">made this gift, which records his</hi>) perpetual devotion.</p>
                
